para.para.body:
In other words: the hyperplane in 
                  \RNr[n]
                perpendicular to 
                  \Vect{n}
                and passing through 
                  \Vect{p}
                consists of all those 
                  \Vect{p}
                such that 
                  (\Vect{x}-\Vect{p})
                dot 
                  \Vect{n}
                is zero.

If 
                     \Vect{x}
                   is the position vector of an arbitrary point in 
                     \RNr[n]
                  , let 
                     \Vect{y}:= \Vect{x} - \Vect{p}
                   be as shown in the picture above. Then 
                     \Vect{x}
                   belongs to the hyperplane perpendicular to 
                     \Vect{n}
                   through 
                     P
                   if and only if 
                     \Vect{y}
                   is perpendicular to 
                     \Vect{n}
                  ; i.e. if and only if
